<br>
Her feet feel heavy in anticipation of the extra cleaning this morning. The tavern was unusually busy last night. <br>
<br>
But then half of a smile steals over her face as she remembers the warrior trying to impress her last night. It seemed he must have traveled across all of Norrath and back to have accomplished all he laid claim to and a few glimpses under the road grime told his tale for him. A young lad with few battles under his belt, but great dreams in his heart. <br>
<br>
Then the loud red head he travelled with couldn't be outdone by his comrade. He spent the next hour telling of his quest for a blessed sword whenever I came within 2 tables of his group. <br>
<br>
I was afraid that he'd come to blows with Faldain the shipwright. Faldain was going to burst unless I let him finish his tale of the 20 pound stonefish he caught... all due to the fishing lure he just invented, of course. The two were desperately trying to outshout each other to get their story told. <br>
<br>
Drixa burst out into a chuckle when she remembered the tale of the impish little rogue. When the powerful mage had been threatening him, the rogue answered his challenge by sneaking up behind him and delivering a wedgie! The whole barroom burst into rounds of laughter as he got up and imitated first the expression on his face and then the queer noise that followed. <br>
<br>
But the story that truly touched my heart was of Jesse. She was so desperate to know if I'd heard of her love Landal. He left with a promise to wed Jesse on his return from Crushbone, but that was over 9 months ago now and we've all heard the tales of what the orcs are capable of. Before Jesse makes her way back onto the streets, I think I'll slip some of this food and a few coins into her packs to help her on her way. And where did I leave that warm cloak that was left in room 3 last week....<br>
<br>
Ahhh... I hear the streets waking. I'd better finish these loaves of bread quickly and be sure all of the ale is ready for another night... and if I'm lucky, some more stories.  <p>Drixa<BR>
Barmaid of the Hero Heart Tavern<BR>
"Pull up a stool, here's an ale to wash the road dust from your throat, and tell me <I>allllllllll</I> about it..."
